xperiences finally came together when he decided to run for elective office as the forceful champion of gays, racial minorities, women, working people, the disabled, and senior citizens. In his last five years, he focused all of his tremendous energy on becoming a successful public figure with a distinct political voice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aElectronic books. 0aGay liberation movementzCaliforniazSan FranciscoxHistoryy20th century. 0aGay liberation movementzCaliforniazSan FranciscoxHistoryy20thcentury. 0aGay menzCaliforniazSan FranciscovBiography. 0aGay politicianszCaliforniazSan FranciscovBiography. 0aJewish menzCaliforniazSan FranciscovBiography. 0aPoliticianszCaliforniazSan FranciscovBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311063899840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030023527240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235272423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300235272/original  a978-3-11-063899-8  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles